                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d643">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">858.248/9–1844: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-28T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 28, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1946. Department’s 1939, September 28, 2 p.m. War Department desires that you
                    immediately inform appropriate Swedish authorities that we are agreeable to the
                    release of the 3 German planes mentioned in your 3895, September 26, 10 p.m.,
                    against the release of as many American airmen as you can obtain. Please cable
                    urgently as soon as their release has been effected.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
